# Check package versions before adding dependencies

Before adding **any** new package dependency — regardless of ecosystem — use WebSearch to verify the current latest stable version. Never assume versions from training data, documentation, or prior conversations, as they go stale quickly.

## Applies to all ecosystems

| Ecosystem | Registry |
|---|---|
| Flutter / Dart | pub.dev |
| Python (uv / pip) | pypi.org |
| Node.js | npmjs.com |
| Any other | check the official registry |

## Process

1. Search: `<package-name> <registry> latest version <current-year>`
2. Confirm the version is **stable** (not alpha/beta/rc) unless a pre-release is explicitly needed
3. Use the exact verified version in `pubspec.yaml`, `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, etc.
4. Update the relevant docs page (e.g. `mintdocs/build/flutter-app.mdx`) to reflect the new version

## Example

```
# ❌ BAD — assumes training data is current
mobile_scanner: ^6.0.0

# ✅ GOOD — verified via WebSearch before writing
mobile_scanner: ^7.2.0
```
